HAPPY BLACK HISTORY MONTH🖤‼️📕📕📚 🌎 

🖤One this 1st week of #BlackHistoryMonth  I Celebrate the young Kings known as “The Greensboro 4” David Richmond, Franklin MCCain, Ezell Blair Jr. (Jibreel Khazan) & Joe McNeil. 👑✊🏾 🖤
My lil bro @realgoodsax 🎷 & I had the Beautiful Privilege of performing for the Ceremony honoring them in 2022🖤🎤🎼

These 4 Aggies 💙💛 sparked the flame 🔥 of CHANGE when they took a STAND by sitting down at the then-whites-only Woolworth's lunch counter in my hometown & refused to move until they were served. 
This Courageous act started a nationwide movement in the push for civil rights and justice for all.
Let’s Always Remember them & All the other Warriors of DOING WHAT’S RIGHT☝🏾 and TEACH our Kids the WHOLE TRUTH about their History and the MANY contributions & SACRIFICES made by others so that THEY can Live A Better FREER LIFE!! 🙏🏾😁✊🏾 & Yes…..We STILL have WORK 2 DO…. 🇺🇸

It is with great sadness that I share the news of the passing of my Beloved Aunt “Mary D.”
Heaven has gained an Angel 😇 
Mary was my Mama’s  youngest sister & a strong, smart, funny, independent Queen 👸🏽. 
When I was little girl I remember going to the airport in Greensboro to wait right at the gate (back when u could ✈️) for her to arrive bk home from The Big City” 🏙 of NYC, where she had a successful career in tele-communications.
I was Always so Proud & inspired by her strong 💪🏾 “Got Get It” spirit! 💕 Even when her health declined over the last few years…she was still da spunkiest resident of her Adult Care facility ☺️💪🏾 Mama 🎹 & I would visit her an “impromptu perform” for all the residents & that made her so proud & made her Smile.🥰
I will miss her dearly, but I  know she is no longer in pain & she is with her big sis now in Heaven & they are both watching over Me, Lyn & Kim and Aunt Fran💕

Please keep my family lifted in prayer as we prepare to say goodbye this week.🙏🏾
Luv u Auntie, 4 ever & ever! 💕

💕☀️ It’s Breast Cancer Awareness Month Yal 💕💕
One of the goals of Breast Cancer Awareness Month is to promote awareness of the condition that will affect 1 in 8 women and 1 in 100 men☝🏾
It’s also intended to be a time fund breast cancer research and stress the importance of EARLY testing and detection💕 

Early Detection SAVED my Life 🙏🏾 & I am HERE…5 years Strong 💪🏾 and counting & So very Grateful for each and EVERY Breath I Take☀️
I know testing can be scary….but KNOWLEDGE  is POWER 💕 

Many of U have shared your personal stories about your own journey or supporting someone on their journey🙏🏾💕☀️ it’s Very healing & Support Is SO important. I salute ur transparency 🎀
Let’s continue to be here 4 each other, listen 👂🏽 , learn and take away ALL stigmas so folks feel like they can talk about this openly and that it’s OK 🥰🙏🏾💕💕💕

Shout out to organizations like @earlierdotorg that I have worked with in my community & the good work they do💕 I ask that each of U find ways that u can help in your communities. 
Some folks Walk for a Cure, Wear pink ribbons 🎀, knit or crochet 🧶 caps or scarfs for chemo patients or donate funds or time☀️ it All helps. 

Throughout this month I’ll be posting different links to ways U can get more involved in this fight & also posting facts for Awareness🤘🏾Please feel free to DM me info or links u think would be helpful to everyone ☀️🙏🏾💕

God Bless u All & keep sharing your stories … it’s HEALING & We R HERE 4 U 🙏🏾💕 Shout out to All my surviving sisters and brothers and prayers to the families of those that have gone on to Glory 😇 we Luv U❤️
